r}}\n\n==Rankings==\n{{Further|2014 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings}}\n{{NCAA Division I FBS CFP ranking movements\n| year            = {{2014}}\n| finalpollweek   = 16\n| cfpfirstweek    = 9\n| AP_pre          = RV\n| coaches_pre     = RV\n| AP_1            = RV\n| coaches_1       = RV\n| AP_2            = RV\n| coaches_2       = RV\n| AP_3            = RV\n| coaches_3       = RV\n| AP_4            = 14\n| coaches_4       = 16\n| AP_5            = 12\n| coaches_5       = 14\n| AP_6            = 3 <small>(2)</small>\n| coaches_6       = 6\n| AP_7            = 1 <small>(45)</small>\n| coaches_7       = 1 <small>(26)</small>\n| AP_8            = 1 <small>(43)</small>\n| coaches_8       = 1 <small>(36)</small>\n| AP_9            = 1 <small>(46)</small>\n| coaches_9       = 1 <small>(41)</small>\n| cfp_9           = 1\n| AP_10           = 1 <small>(45)</small>\n| coaches_10      = 1 <small>(40)</small>\n| cfp_10          = 1\n| AP_11           = 1 <small>(48)</small>\n| coaches_11      = 1 <small>(41)</small>\n| cfp_11          = 1\n| AP_12           = 4\n| coaches_12      = 4\n| cfp_12          = 4\n| AP_13           = 4\n| coaches_13      = 4\n| cfp_13          = 4\n| AP_14           = 10\n| coaches_14      = 10\n| cfp_14          = 10\n| AP_15           = 8\n| coaches_15      = 8\n| cfp_15          = 7\n| AP_16           = 11\n| coaches_16      =12\n}}\n\nFollowing MSU's win over Auburn, the team was ranked Number 1 in the AP Poll for the first time in the program's history. That also marked \"the fastest [rise to the top] in AP Top 25 history.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Mississippi State Completes Fastest Ascent to No. 1 in AP Top 25 History|first=Eric|last=Vander Voort|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/poll-position/2014-10-12/mississippi-state-completes-fastest-ascent-no-1-ap-top-25|publisher=National Collegiate Athletic Association|date=October 12, 2014|accessdate=October 15, 2014}}</ref> The previous mark was six weeks by [[1954 Ohio State Buckeyes footb